column7: Determine representatives each day when winner represents last day, and all prior days alternate
between top vote getter for each party, where a “party” must get 5% of the vote to qualify for representation,
and representation is split so that each representatives serve a percentage of days in office equivalent
to their vote share relative to that of the other qualifying top finishers, and unaffiliated candidates are all
considered to be in a party separate from all other parties and all other unaffiliated candidates.
